53:50.960 --> 53:58.960
I'm just going to start picking from the book.

53:58.960 --> 54:25.960
I wonder if maybe I'll read a couple of poems that I don't normally read out loud.

54:25.960 --> 54:32.960
There's still quite narrative of the poems, but they make more lyric leaps in Al-Ajean

54:32.960 --> 54:36.600
Valentine than many of my other poems do.

54:36.600 --> 54:42.960
So this one's called Undrowning.

54:42.960 --> 54:45.720
In Spanish, there's a word called disallerci.

54:45.720 --> 54:51.240
I learned that word from my friend Jessica and it sort of gave me this poem.

54:51.240 --> 54:57.240
She was going through a hard time and her mom said that you have to undrown yourself.

54:57.240 --> 54:59.240
Yeah.

54:59.240 --> 55:01.440
Undrowning.

55:01.440 --> 55:05.320
Who needs to be convinced of loneliness in murmurs?

55:05.320 --> 55:12.040
In the palimpsest of a few words rising out of a sentence you don't understand, unless

55:12.040 --> 55:15.400
it's whispered directly into your fingers.

55:15.400 --> 55:18.560
The rain itself isn't terrible.

55:18.560 --> 55:26.360
But sometimes I believe whole oceans are lifted in the name of some worshiped fury and dropped

55:26.360 --> 55:30.120
into our eyes mid-life.

55:30.120 --> 55:37.000
You tell me the word is disallerci, which is to say you've already drowned.

55:37.000 --> 55:43.640
And to undrown you must recall how the light of Venice's lamps and the stars long traveled

55:43.640 --> 55:50.560
a reverent burn break on the wake of a small boat, ferrying you and a couple friends.

55:50.560 --> 55:58.640
One you now grieve, another an opera singer, drunk her hair you remember sweeping over

55:58.640 --> 56:00.800
the prowl.

56:00.800 --> 56:08.800
If the gondolier speaks a word of English, it is yes, which is one of two words in the

56:08.800 --> 56:14.600
language to contain so many disparate categories of sadness.

56:14.600 --> 56:22.920
I mean in the whole of one syllable, half a universe stays afloat, sinks, swims back

56:22.920 --> 56:30.520
up with too much liquor or wine in its blood, and in drowning or its opposite, a life doesn't

56:30.520 --> 56:33.800
flash before your very eyes.

56:33.800 --> 56:40.880
But if I say the multitudes of ghosts put to sleep by centuries of conquerors awaken in

56:40.880 --> 56:41.880
your veins.

56:41.880 --> 56:48.120
And you must answer them with a grief that is neither famous nor deadly.

56:48.120 --> 56:50.360
It's even simpler than that.

56:50.360 --> 56:55.800
One Saturday night you sit under the slant ceiling of your cramped kitchen in a winter

56:55.800 --> 57:02.480
that's lasted a few extra days into spring, doing precise damage to a bottle of coconut

57:02.480 --> 57:06.400
rum that will pay you four times back.

57:06.400 --> 57:12.400
You turn up the sad tangos your lovely shit-talking father used to sing, he who could dream in

57:12.400 --> 57:17.360
the steel language of flight, and you weep.

57:17.360 --> 57:22.760
Your lamentation counts you squarely among the living.

57:22.760 --> 57:24.280
Get either.

57:24.280 --> 57:31.600
I'm sorry a beautiful young man you once laughed with under the near blaze of a foreign sky

57:31.600 --> 57:38.520
while an opera singer slammed her melismatic eyes into the stone and glass of a city sinking

57:38.520 --> 57:43.040
into its shallow glacial canals is dead.

57:43.040 --> 57:48.000
We can't call up all the wreckage of generations.

57:48.000 --> 57:52.040
Do not forget you are witness to a scent.

57:52.040 --> 57:54.640
Tonight sleep well.

57:54.640 --> 58:01.800
When solitude calls it doesn't mean to kill but offers the kind of sight one earns when

58:01.800 --> 58:07.400
you've lain a long time still.

58:07.400 --> 58:15.000
It's a beauty.

58:15.000 --> 58:29.040
Let me read Despely d'Ardiente.

58:29.040 --> 58:31.960
I was teaching at an MFA program in the hall.

58:31.960 --> 58:35.760
You can teach a line.

58:35.760 --> 58:38.800
You can teach meter, you can teach rhythm, you can teach form.

58:38.800 --> 58:44.440
There's a lot of things that you can teach.

58:44.440 --> 58:53.480
The hardest thing to teach, maybe it's impossible to teach, is how to make a poem blaze.

58:53.480 --> 59:00.000
This is my urging towards my students to make it blaze.

59:00.000 --> 59:03.440
Despely d'Ardiente.

59:03.440 --> 59:11.160
Dear feverless, dear poets, dear love sick ones now cured.

59:11.160 --> 59:16.840
There are bloodless battles to be won, but stout your maw with your finest curses.

59:16.840 --> 59:19.400
Yap your demons to their proper graves.

59:19.400 --> 59:23.400
O meek weepers, asymmetries, be kissed.

59:23.400 --> 59:26.280
Let the trash stack in the kitchen.

59:26.280 --> 59:28.720
Keep your lover a full day from work.

59:28.720 --> 59:36.360
O sweet neglect, O nectarine, those bitter pits are meant for more than nibbling.

59:36.360 --> 59:38.240
There is a holy jump off.

59:38.240 --> 59:40.240
There is a funky genesis.

59:40.240 --> 59:45.240
There is a reason love and jive kind of rhyme.

59:45.240 --> 59:48.760
You oblong fruit not three days ripe.

59:48.760 --> 59:53.720
Somewhere in you lies the science of typhoons, a dream of strings.

59:53.720 --> 59:59.840
Oh dirty word, oh first murder, oh cocoa butter whiff on a smoky bus.

59:59.840 --> 01:00:05.680
There are theories were made of mostly nothing but motion.

01:00:05.680 --> 01:00:07.680
Oh dap tooth guitar.

01:00:07.680 --> 01:00:14.320
Oh sound hole, you far away drum, you slang mouth blessing, you long time, you chamberless

01:00:14.320 --> 01:00:15.320
sex step.

01:00:15.320 --> 01:00:20.400
Let me leave you with a few last words.

01:00:20.400 --> 01:00:29.240
When mad dogs break chains to run at you, charge back.

01:00:29.240 --> 01:00:31.240
Bear your very teeth.

01:00:31.240 --> 01:00:34.360
No monster I promise outruns you.

01:00:34.360 --> 01:00:38.040
Let them on the ankle with a stick, chase the bastards down.

01:00:38.040 --> 01:00:43.600
Listen, this vertigo, this wreckage, this bad ballad straining the thickest tendons of

01:00:43.600 --> 01:00:44.600
your legs.

01:00:44.600 --> 01:00:49.520
Oh darling sleepers, may you wake in the middle of the night strange.

01:00:49.520 --> 01:00:51.640
Sounds you champions of laughter.

01:00:51.640 --> 01:00:54.480
All you have to do is speak simply.

01:00:54.480 --> 01:00:56.360
Your business is the truth.

01:00:56.360 --> 01:01:01.120
Your hearts catastrophe is just a little a histories twisted bulwark.

01:01:01.120 --> 01:01:07.880
If there were not a sky within your chest worth breaking, believe me, you would have

01:01:07.880 --> 01:01:11.120
stopped all this singing by now.

01:01:11.120 --> 01:01:17.040
Hey, that's so great.

01:01:17.040 --> 01:01:43.840
I guess I could tell a story about that poem.

01:01:43.840 --> 01:01:49.160
